1. PREAMBLE
-----------

This license governs the use, reproduction, modification, and distribution
of the OpenAuth Authenticator software ("the Software"), an open-source
two-factor authentication application for Android devices. By obtaining,
using, or distributing the Software, you accept and agree to be bound by
the terms and conditions of this license.

The OpenAuth Authenticator Project ("the Project") is committed to
providing a secure, privacy-respecting, and transparent authenticator
application. This license is designed to protect end users, contributors,
and the integrity of the Software while promoting open collaboration.


2. DEFINITIONS
--------------

"Software" means the source code, object code, documentation, resources,
and all associated materials contained in the OpenAuth Authenticator
repository.

"Contributor" means any individual or entity that submits code,
documentation, or other materials to the Project.

"User" means any individual or entity that downloads, installs, or
operates the Software.

"Distribution" means any conveyance of the Software or derivative works
to third parties.

"Derivative Work" means any modification, enhancement, or adaptation of
the Software, in whole or in part.

"Vault" means the encrypted storage system containing user secrets,
including but not limited to OTP secret keys, PIN hashes, and backup data.


