5. SECURITY AND PRIVACY OBLIGATIONS
------------------------------------

The Software implements cryptographic security measures to protect user
data. Any distribution or derivative work must:

    a) Maintain or exceed the security standards implemented in the
       original Software, including but not limited to:

       - AES-256-GCM encryption for all secret data
       - Argon2id, Scrypt, or PBKDF2 key derivation with minimum
         iteration counts as specified in security documentation
       - Android Keystore hardware-backed key storage where available
       - Biometric authentication binding with invalidation on enrollment
         changes
       - Automatic clipboard clearing with IS_SENSITIVE flag on
         supported platforms
       - Memory wiping of cryptographic material after use

    b) Not introduce telemetry, analytics, tracking, or any data
       collection mechanism that transmits user data off-device without
       explicit, informed user consent;

    c) Not introduce backdoors, master keys, or any mechanism that
       weakens the cryptographic protections of the Vault;

    d) Clearly disclose any network communication initiated by the
       Software and obtain user consent before transmission;

    e) Maintain the zero-knowledge architecture where the service provider
       cannot access user secrets under any circumstances.


